@NODE INSTALL "How do I get this up and running?"

The recommended installation procedure involves copying the library
into @{b}EGS:Libs@{ub} and then entering @{b}egs_real.library@{ub} into
the External Screen Library string gadget. Click on this button to

      @{"  copy the egs_real.library to EGS:Libs  " SYSTEM "c:copy egs_real.library EGS:libs/egs_real.library"}


@ENDNODE INSTALL


@NODE GADGETS "What does this button do?"

When you open an external screen with egs_real.library for the first
time you will see a window. It will have a listview containing all
the available EGS screen modes and three gadgets. After you have
chosen your desired screen mode by clicking on it's name in the list
view you can either Cancel the selection, Use it just this time or
Save the settings. When you choose "Save", the environment variables
@{b}EGS/R3D_ScreenMode@{ub} and @{b}EGS/R3D_ScreenDepth@{ub} are created. These
will contain your prefered screen mode and the depth at which this
screen should be opened. By default the highest possible depth is
used. You can force a different depth by modifying the environment
variable.

There will not be any requesters asking for a screen mode the next
time you choose to open an external screen from within Real 3D,
providing you chose to save the settings. You can change the screen
mode at any time from within Real 3D by selecting the menu item
"Project/External Screen/Set Modes".


@ENDNODE GADGETS



