@NODE BUGS "Real 3D has many bugs, here are some of them"

Real 3D is a huge package, and yes, there are some bugs in it. They
exhibit themselves as very strange @{b}features@{ub} in egs_real.library

 · When the external screen is opened it is cleared to a very strange,
   blue/green colour. This bug is caused by Real 3D passing a dud value
   to the ClearScreen function, just after it opens the external screen.
   I think I know how to implement a workaround, but I'd rather RealSoft
   fixed their program :-)

 · Whenever a box begins rendering (using the Autobox feature in version
   3 of Real 3D) the screen forces it's way to the front. Yes, this is
   Real 3D's fault too. It calls the initialiser function for every box
   render start instead of calling it only at the begining of the entire
   render.

 · The above is also related to the fact that the screen is not cleared
   between renders. If egs_real.library cleared the screen at the start
   of every render you would end up with the second box clearing the
   first one!

@ENDNODE BUGS




